Cagliari club president Massimo Cellino,  head of a cereal trader, was charged with embezzling 24 billion lira (15  million dollars) from the European Union, a court source said Tuesday.
Cellino, 38, was accused of making illegal claims for semolina exports to  non-European Union countries, mainly to Algeria.
He was detained when he went to police headquarters to see examining  magistrates.
